en_696276_0	Arrangements have been made to provide teaching appointments to 4286 National Diploma holders in Teaching.
en_696276_1	The ceremony to hand over appointment letters will be held at Temple Trees under the patronage of Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe.
en_696276_2	These students who have followed courses in 31 subjects in Sinhala, Tamil and English mediums in 19 Colleges of Education are considered as Diplomated Professional Teachers of Education.
en_696276_3	Of these, 2340 have followed courses in Sinhala medium and 1300 in Tamil and 646 in English medium.
en_696276_4	The Ministry of Education states that these students have completed one year internship after completing the two year course.
en_696276_5	Minister AkilaVirajKariyawasam has instructed the officials to send these teachers to schools where shortage of teachers is present.
